4.3

Simulation Parameters

The microscopic traÔ¨Éc simulation of P.I.E was initialized with the parameters listed in Table 2.
Parameters such as a, b and li are modeled as distributions to take into account heterogeneous
driving behaviors and vehicle classes respectively. In order to obtain a ballpark Ô¨Ågure for
congestion in terms of vehicle density, we make use of the simplest of the Lighthill Whitham
Richards (LWR) models using a triangular fundamental diagram [14]. The critical density for
congested traÔ¨Éc œÅc , according to the LWR model is given by V0 √óTI+lef f . Here lef f represents
the minimum distance headway which is the sum of average vehicle length and minimum gap
s0 . Vehicle density exceeding œÅc generally implies a congested traÔ¨Éc Ô¨Çow regime.
Based on the parameters listed in Table 2, œÅc works out to around 31 vehicles/km/lane.
Thus we consider traÔ¨Éc greater than 93 vehicles/km, (assuming the minimum of three lanes)
as congested. In fact, each traÔ¨Éc scenario (discussed later) is also characterized based on the
average vehicle density during the simulation period of 2 hours. It is to be noted that the
LWR based triangular fundamental diagram overestimates the critical density since it ignores
vehicular interactions such as lane changes and assumes homogeneous traÔ¨Éc, but nevertheless
serves as a rough estimate for congestion.

4.4

Simulation Scenarios

The traÔ¨Éc density (œÅ) in number of vehicles/km across the expressway is controlled by varying
the average inter-arrival rates at all sources along P.I.E. The density of the entire expressway
is computed at the end of the two hour simulation by counting the number of distinct agents
per kilometer of the road. To simulate heavy congestion along P.I.E the parameter Œªs for all
on-ramps was set to a uniform random number between 2.0 sec and 2.5 sec (representing a Ô¨Çow
of 1800-1440 vehicles/hour) while Œªs for the Ô¨Årst and only source link of P.I.E was set to 1.0 sec
(3600 vehicles per hour). The sampling period of all probe vehicles unless stated otherwise is
